{"id": "730945", "revid": "90173", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=730945", "title": "Lukko", "text": "Rauman Lukko (Finnish for \"lock\") is a Finnish sports club based in Rauma, Finland, best known for its men's professional ice hockey team. The club was founded as Rauma Woodin Lukko in 1936. The representative team currently plays in the Finnish Liiga, the premier men's professional ice hockey league in Finland. They play their home games in the \u00c4ij\u00e4nsuo Arena, which has a capacity of 5,400 spectators. Lukko won the SM-sarja in 1963 and won the Liiga championship in 2021. Until 2023 the club also had a top-tier women's representative ice hockey team, which played in the Naisten Liiga, and a top-tier women's representative pes\u00e4pallo team, which plays in the Superpesis.\nHonours.\nDomestic.\nLiiga\nSM-sarja\n\"Other awards for the club:\"\nPre-season.\nFinnish Cup"}
